# Before You Start

1. **Step 1 (HARD GATE) — Install the Dataverse-skills plugin.** Every Dataverse operation is delegated to the [microsoft/Dataverse-skills](https://github.com/microsoft/Dataverse-skills) plugin — first-class, only-supported path. Do this first; the agent stops on any Dataverse work until it's installed and MCP tools are reachable. Needs Python 3 + `pip install PowerPlatform-Dataverse-Client pandas`. Install (Copilot **CLI** ≠ VS Code Copilot chat): Copilot CLI → `/plugin install dataverse@awesome-copilot`; Claude → `claude plugin install dataverse@claude-plugins-official`. Restart editor, then verify.
2. **Step 2 — Publisher prefix** (2–8 lowercase letters, no numbers/hyphens). Namespace for everything; cannot change after data exists. Record as `PUBLISHER_PREFIX`.
3. **Step 3 — Create the publisher (not by hand in Maker Portal).** Wizard's **Solution & Publisher** step or the **dv-solution** skill creates it (reuse over duplication).
4. **Step 4 — Create environments** — Dev (required), Test, Prod, each Dataverse-enabled. Record each URL.
5. **Step 5 — Create the solution (also created for you, not hand-built)** bound to the publisher, via the wizard or **dv-solution**. Added to the solution on first `pac code push` (`-s`).
6. **Step 6 — Create connections** in each environment for every connector, **before** importing the solution.
7. **Step 7 — Register the App Registration** as an Application User in each environment.
8. **Step 8 — Verify** with `pac auth select`, `pac org who`, `pac solution list`.

Full details: `.github/instructions/00-before-you-start.instructions.md`
